To some extent. Lets say who are the companies will have datacenter? A medium to large scale company. With my experience I don't see many enterprise companies completely abandoning their data center. Most of the companies are following hybrid cloud models, in which case they do have to maintain DC. Also, i read an article a year back (i couldn't find) which speaks about how difficult it is to find Data Center engineers. (because of their unique experience knowledge on both H/W and S/W).   